# Git commit + push — summary in commit message

When you **`git commit`** and **`git push`** (because the user asked, or to ship completed work), the commit must record **what shipped**, not only a short subject line.

## Commit message shape

Use a **subject** (≤72 chars, imperative) plus a **body** (the “comment” in git history):

```text
Short subject summarizing the batch.

## Summary
One or two sentences on why this batch ships.

## Features
- Bullet: user-visible feature or data model addition
- …

## Bug fixes
- Bullet: what was broken and how it was fixed
- …

## Notes (optional)
- Tests, docs, migration caveats
```

- Pull bullets from the **latest open** section(s) in **`GoDiveMVP/cursor/change_log.md`** being shipped (and **`app_summary.md`** if helpful).
- **Features** vs **bug fixes**: put regressions, wrong values, missing UI, and reliability issues under **Bug fixes**; new capability under **Features**.
- If the batch is fixes-only, omit **Features** (or write “None.”). If features-only, omit **Bug fixes**.

## Workflow with changelog

1. **Preflight (required)** — Per **`xcode-test-only-when-asked.mdc`**: iPhone 17 sim **`clean`** → **`clean build-for-testing`** → **`test`**; fix errors, failures, and warnings (**`xcode-fix-build-warnings.mdc`**). **Do not commit or push** until green.
2. Ensure **`change_log.md`** / **`app_summary.md`** reflect the work (**`.cursor/rules/changelog-app-summary-sync.mdc`**).
3. **`git commit`** with subject + body via HEREDOC (see user commit rules).
4. **`git push`** when requested.
5. Mark shipped section(s) **`(pushed)`** per **`.cursor/rules/changelog-mark-pushed-on-git-push.mdc`** — include that edit in the commit when possible; otherwise a tiny follow-up commit after push.

## Do not

- **Commit or push** without a green iPhone 17 simulator preflight (**`build-for-testing`** + **`test`**, 0 project warnings).
- Push with **only** a one-line subject when the batch includes multiple features or bug fixes.
- Paste the entire change log; synthesize scannable bullets.
- Skip the body because the user will “read it in chat” — the body is for **`git log`** and reviewers.

## Example

```text
Fix dive map pin, tank volume display, and add equipment linking.

## Summary
Ship dive equipment association, reliable map pin + overview sheet UX,
and corrected default tank volume for display and RMV.

## Features
- Link locker gear to dives; tank tab list + add sheet; auto-add on import.
- Settings → Default tank (AL80, AL63, ST100, ST120).

## Bug fixes
- MKMapView pin no longer disappears after camera updates.
- Site name on overview sheet header; pin-only map (no truncated callout).
- Tank volume uses rated cu ft (not mis-parsed UDDF L or FIT volume-used).
- Tab switch map→tank no longer flashes minimized depth chart.
```
